ABAE510F4E511586584FE19B7515648E: Copies current grid contents onto the next available blank page. If no pages are blank, this button is disabled.
4774DC6449E63DC30D19FA8479904E1C: Removes all notes from the grid on the current page.
0384F3134924BE92014AC8B9726D7874: Selects which drum note will be used when placing notes in the grid.

UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.Style.Descr: Adjusts the rate of the sequencer output. "Straight" will output at 1/16 note rate. "Triplet" will output notes in a shuffle feel at 1/8 note triplet rate.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.AllowPortSe: Determines if the Patchwork Tool can access any cable input or output ports on the device.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.EnabledOnPh: Determines the game phases during which the device will be enabled. Pre-game includes all phases prior to start of game (like the pre-game lobby or countdown to start of game.) This setting does not affect Edit Mode.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.Presets.Des: Determines whether the preset pattern should be copied to the current page.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.Disable.Des: Disables the device when an event occurs.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.Enable.Desc: Enables the device when an event occurs.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.LegalInfo.D: Please note: Use of a Patchwork audio device is limited to the creation of new and original musical works.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.Page.Descri: Select which page is shown and played on the Note Grid. Each page can contain its own pattern of notes.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.PresetSelec: Selects a pattern of notes in a particular musical style.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.NoteOut.Des: Sets the destination for this device's Note Out cable.
Sets the inputs for this device's Auto Page toggle.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.PageIn.Desc: Sets the inputs for this device's Page knob.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.PresetIn.De: Sets the inputs for this device's Preset carousel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.PresetToggl: Sets the inputs for this device's Preset toggle.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.TripletIn.D: Sets the inputs for this device's Triplet toggle.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.AutoPage.De: Toggles whether the sequencer cycles through every populated page, or remains on the current page only.
Triggers an event when the device is disabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.OnEnabled.D: Triggers an event when the device is enabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.AutoPagePla: When enabled, Auto Page will include blank pages when cycling through pages automatically.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_FabricDrumSequencer_C.bLoop.Descr: When set to OFF, the sequencer will play through its pattern once when enabled, then return to its disabled state.
